We've released a new QuickBooks Desktop integration utilizing Intuit's Web Connector for a simpler and faster SMB link journey.

As of xxx date all new connectors will use this new flow.

<!--truncate-->

## What's changed?

- Replaced old bespoke app with new blah
- Reduced the number of installation steps for SMB users in the link flow, now performing the installation via a web browser
- Simplified the processes to connect to QuickBooks Desktop on Right Networks or QuickBooks Enterprise for cloud, now you no longer need to go through the RN application process.
- Better diagnostics to triage connector issues

Read more about this in xxx

## What does this mean for you?

If you have existing QBD connections share the existing link url (screenshot) with your SMB customers to trigger the new flow. This will initiate the new flow, completition of which will establish the new connector.

:::tip Link URL

To locate existing link urls do this...

:::

Any new connections, as of xxx date this will automatically be via the new link flow using the new connector.
